1. Feature Name
Archetype Builder
2. Goal
Enable users to define their story's main character by selecting from 12 Jungian archetypes, understanding archetype combinations, exploring dark sides (too much/too little), and mapping character transformation journeys. This feature brings the Storyteller Tactics archetype framework to life, helping users create compelling, psychologically grounded characters that resonate with audiences.
3. User Story
As a user developing my story,
I want to build a rich, multi-dimensional character using proven archetypes,
So that my character feels authentic, relatable, and drives the story forward with clear motivations and transformation potential.
4. Functional Requirements
4.1 Core Functionality
4.1.1 Mode-Specific Behavior
Quick Mode (15-20 min):

AI suggests 1 primary archetype based on story type and audience
User can accept or choose from simplified grid (12 archetypes)
No combination or dark side exploration
Saves primary archetype only

Comprehensive Mode (45-60 min):

Full archetype grid with detailed exploration
Primary + secondary archetype combinations
Dark sides (too much/too little) configuration
Character journey mapping (transformation arc)
Voice and values customization

4.1.2 Archetype Selection Paths
Users can choose from 3 selection methods:
Path A: AI-Suggested (Recommended for Quick Mode)

System analyzes story type, audience, conflict
Recommends 1-3 archetypes with explanation
User can accept or explore alternatives

Path B: Archetype Grid (Visual browsing)

12 archetype cards in 4Ã—3 grid
Each card shows: icon, name, tagline, core value
Click for full details before selecting

Path C: Deep Builder (Comprehensive Mode)

Guided questionnaire (8-10 questions)
Progressive archetype revelation based on answers
Personalized archetype recommendation with explanation

4.2 The 12 Archetypes
Complete archetype library with full details:
